        "summary": {
          "diffs": [
            {
              "file": "bench-artifacts/cache-api.md",
              "patch": "Index: bench-artifacts/cache-api.md\n===================================================================\n--- bench-artifacts/cache-api.md\t\n+++ bench-artifacts/cache-api.md\t\n@@ -0,0 +1,61 @@\n+# Cache API\n+\n+## createCache()\n+\n+Creates a new cache instance with an internal `Map` for storing key-value pairs.\n+\n+```js\n+import { createCache } from 'path/to/cache'\n+\n+const cache = createCache()\n+// cache is now an object with get, set, delete, and clear methods\n+```\n+\n+### Methods\n+\n+The `createCache()` function returns an object with the following methods:\n+\n+#### get(key)\n+\n+Retrieves a value from the cache by its key. Returns the cached value if found, otherwise `undefined`.\n+\n+```js\n+cache.get('my-key')\n+```\n+\n+#### set(key, value)\n+\n+Stores a value in the cache under the specified key. Returns the provided value.\n+\n+```js\n+cache.set('my-key', 'my-value')\n+```\n+\n+#### delete(key)\n+\n+Removes an entry from the cache by its key. Returns `true` if the key existed, `false` otherwise.\n+\n+```js\n+cache.delete('my-key')\n+```\n+\n+#### clear()\n+\n+Empties the entire cache, removing all key-value pairs.\n+\n+```js\n+cache.clear()\n+```\n+\n+## Usage\n+\n+```js\n+import { createCache } from 'cache.mjs'\n+\n+const cache = createCache()\n+\n+cache.set('user:1', { id: 1, name: 'Alice' })\n+const user = cache.get('user:1')\n+cache.delete('user:1')\n+cache.clear()\n+```\n",
              "additions": 61,
              "deletions": 0,
              "status": "added"
            }
          ]
        },
